data.enText: the faint light or the period of time at the end of the day after the sun has gone down

data.chText: 在朦胧的暮色中很难看清他。
data.enText: It was hard to see him clearly in the twilight .

data.chText: 黄昏时分我们沿着海滩散步。
data.enText: We went for a walk along the beach at twilight .
the final stage of sth when it becomes weaker or less important than it was
the twilight years (= the last years of your life)
used to describe a state in which things are strange and mysterious, or where things are kept secret and do not seem to be part of the real world
the twilight world of the occult

data.chText: 他们生活在社会边缘的过渡区域。
data.enText: They lived in the twilight zone on the fringes of society.

data.chText: （局面或思想领域）朦胧的，模糊的，界限不清的
data.enText: used to describe a situation or area of thought that is not clearly defined

word_means: 朦胧的，模糊的，界限不清的
simple_means.memory_skill: twi 二，两 + light 光 → 黑白光交替 → 黎明

means: (局面或思想领域)朦胧的，模糊的，界限不清的

tr: the diffused light from the sky when the sun is below the horizon but its rays are refracted by the atmosphere of the earth
a condition of decline following successes
example: in the twilight of the empire

tr: the time of day immediately following sunset
example: they finished before the fall of night

value.def: Twilight is the time just before night when the daylight has almost gone but when it is not completely dark.

example.ex: They returned at twilight, and set off for one of the promenade bars.
example.tran: 他们黄昏时分回来，然后去了一家步行街酒吧。

value.def: Twilight is the small amount of light that there is outside just after the sun has gone down.
The twilight of a particular period of time is the final stages of it, when the most important events have already happened.

example.ex: Now both men are in the twilight of their careers...
example.tran: 现在两人的事业都到了没落期。

example.ex: I am getting old. I am in the twilight of my life.
example.tran: 我老了，到了生命的暮年。

example.ex: …the twilight years of the Habsburg empire.
example.tran: 哈布斯堡帝国的衰落时期

value.def: A twilight state or a twilight zone is a situation of confusion or uncertainty, which seems to exist between two different states or categories.

example.ex: They fell into that twilight zone between military personnel and civilian employees.
example.tran: 他们成了军队人员与平民雇员之间身份界定不清的人。

value.tran: 蒙眬的;含混的;界限模糊的
